description: Nvidia's AI summit in Mumbai saw CEO Jensen Huang praise India's tech capabilities while Reliance chairman Mukesh Ambani announced an AI infrastructure partnership. Indian companies like TCS, Tata Communications, and Infosys launched new AI initiatives, as Huang highlighted India's key role in language model innovation.
title: Nvidia CEO sees India as an 'AI giant in the making'

description: The United States has welcomed the India-China LAC agreement that ended the eastern Ladakh military standoff. US ambassador Eric Garcetti emphasized America's support for India's efforts to maintain strategic interests and respect borders, underscoring the pact’s positive implications for global and regional stability.
title: Good day in Indo-Pacific: US welcomes India-China LAC deal

description: To accommodate the festive rush during Deepawali and Chhath, Indian Railways is operating at least 7,000 additional special trains from October 1 to November 30. This is a 60% increase over last year's 4,429 trains. Specific arrangements include extra ticket counters, catering units, and enhanced security at stations.
title: Railways to run 7,000 extra trains for Diwali, Chhath

description: A special court in Bengaluru found Satish Sail, Karwar's Congress MLA, and five others guilty in the Rs 250-crore Belekeri port scam related to the theft and export of iron ore seized between 2006-07 and 2010-11. The judge directed the CBI to take the convicts into custody.
title: Congress MLA among 6 convicted in Karnataka iron ore scam

description: The Supreme Court permits Ajit Pawar's faction to use the 'clock' symbol for Maharashtra assembly polls, but mandates disclosure in all media about ongoing litigation over the party's name and symbol. Ajit Pawar must submit an undertaking to comply with this directive.
title: SC allows Ajit's party to use 'clock' symbol with rider

description: The allure of life in the US drives thousands of Indians, mainly Gujaratis, to risk illegal immigration despite dangers. US FY 2024 saw 90,415 Indians caught at borders, with shifts from the Mexico route to Canada. Enhanced vigilance has altered migration patterns.
title: 10 Indians per hour tried to enter US illegally in last one year: Data shows

description: Jammu and Kashmir CM Omar Abdullah meets PM Modi to push for the early restoration of J&K's statehood, presenting a resolution passed by the assembly. Abdullah also discusses security, development works, and road connectivity projects with relevant ministers, emphasizing the region's constitutional rights and unique identity.
title: Omar Abdullah calls on PM, seeks early statehood restoration for J&K

description: Khalistani terrorist Gurpatwant Pannun has demanded the shutdown of CRPF schools starting November 26, offering a $1 million reward for information on Union Home Minister Amit Shah's foreign trips. This follows a blast near a CRPF school, with Pannun accusing CRPF and its officials of historical atrocities against Sikhs and extrajudicial killings in Punjab.
title: Pannun calls for shutdown of CRPF schools, offers Shah info 'reward'
Maharashtra nod to prosecute 2 doctors in Porsche case
Government launches Gram panchayat-level weather forecasting
SC: Aadhaar cannot be authoritative date of birth proof

description: NCP (SCP), led by Sharad Pawar, announced its first list of candidates for the Maharashtra assembly polls, including 11 of its 12 sitting MLAs. The faction will compete against Ajit Pawar's NCP in 13 key constituencies, including Baramati, highlighting internal party strife. The election outcome will determine the dominant faction in western Maharashtra.
title: Sharad Pawar names 45 nominees in 1st list; NCP vs NCP in 13 seats

description: In a pioneering move in India, Ratan Tata has allocated provisions in his will for lifelong care of his German Shepherd, Tito. Additionally, Tata's will includes distributions to his foundation, family, dedicated house staff, and executive assistant Shantanu Naidu. Major assets such as real estate and stakes in Tata Sons will be transferred to the Ratan Tata Endowment Foundation.
title: 'Unlimited' care for pet dog Tito, share for butler in Ratan Tata will
Day after 85-85-85 pact, Congress neta says party will contest 104 seats

description: Sebi chairperson Madhabi Puri Buch cited 'personal exigencies' to skip a Parliament's PAC meeting, leading to a clash between PAC head K C Venugopal and NDA members. They accused Venugopal of unilateral decisions, culminating in a protest lodged with Lok Sabha Speaker Om Birla.
title: Buch skips PAC meet, Rahul asks 'who's behind plan to shield her'

description: Indian and Chinese troops have begun phased disengagement at Depsang and Demchok in eastern Ladakh, dismantling temporary posts established since May 2020. The new patrolling pact ensures pre-informed patrol schedules to avoid confrontations, with the process expected to take around a week for verification and compliance.
title: India, China begin troop disengagement in eastern Ladakh

description: A sessions court in Karnataka has sentenced 98 people to life imprisonment and three others to five years in jail for caste-related violence against Dalits in Marakumbi village. The 2014 incident involved a mob assault that led to torching of Dalit huts. Over 100 individuals were convicted after a decade-long trial.
title: 98 get life term for 2014 violence against Dalits in Karnataka

description: After a marathon meeting with Union Home Minister Amit Shah, Maharashtra's Mahayuti allies narrowed their seat-sharing differences down to 12 seats, primarily in Mumbai. BJP may contest over 155 seats, Shiv Sena around 80-85, and NCP (Ajit Pawar) the rest. There's a joint pledge to stem rebellions and avoid 'friendly contests.'
title: BJP and allies narrow down differences to about 12 seats
3 dead, 1 injured as truck runs overgroup changing tyre on UP highway

description: Horoscope Today: Read daily horoscope predictions for October 25, 2024. Know all about the astrological events and influences that will be affecting each of the 12 zodiac signs. Get ready to discover what the stars have in store for you today.
title: Horoscope Today, October 25, 2024: Read your astrological predictions

description: Pakistani authorities released Bushra Bibi, wife of imprisoned former PM Imran Khan, from Rawalpindi jail following her bail approval in a graft case. She had been detained for nearly nine months on corruption charges, relating to the mishandling of state gifts. Her release was welcomed by PTI.
title: Imran’s wife Bushra Bibi released after Islamabad HC grants bail in graft case
Confiscated grenade goes off in Baramulla court, cop injured
19-year-old barber from UP shot at in south Kashmir

description: Rahul Gandhi criticized SEBI Chairperson Madhabi Puri Buch for not appearing before the Parliament's Public Accounts Committee, suggesting she was being shielded from accountability. The PAC meeting was postponed after Buch informed the committee of her inability to travel to Delhi.
title: 'Why is Madhabi Buch reluctant?': Rahul after Sebi chief skips PAC meeting

description: In a tragic terror ambush near Botapathri along the LoC, two soldiers and two porters were killed on a military truck in Baramulla, Kashmir. This marks the fourth attack since CM Omar Abdullah's government took office, bringing total security casualties since May to 24.
title: 2 soldiers, 2 porters killed in J&K attack on army truck

description: In Missouri's St. Louis County, an elderly man was forced to leave his home after his daughter discovered he was living in squalor with 175 cats. The daughter gained access to the house after her mother passed away, revealing the deplorable conditions. The daughter said a relative came to stay with their parents who blocked everyone's entry to the house and that went on for years.
title: Bizarre! US man lived with 175 cats, daughter was not allowed to enter

description: Pakistani security forces killed nine insurgents, including a key leader, during a shootout in Bajaur, Khyber Pakhtunkhwa. Troops seized weapons and ammunition from the militants' hideout. This operation comes amid a surge in militant attacks following the collapse of a truce with the Tehreek-e-Taliban Pakistan (TTP) in November 2022.
title: Pakistan forces kill 9 militants in restive northwest

description: ​These days, the word Nazi or fascist or Hitler is used with such wanton abandon that it has ceased to have any meaning and tells us more about the user than the subject. It’s a sign of desperation and flop sweat. And the Democrats – after swapping Harris for Biden – are reeking of desperation as the election enters the home stretch.
title: US Election Top 10: Calling Trump the F-word shows Dems are getting desperate

description: Cyclone Dana is nearing the coasts of Odisha and West Bengal, with landfall expected between October 24-25, bringing wind speeds of 100-120 km/h. Extensive evacuations are underway, schools are closed, and flights are suspended. PM Modi and other officials are monitoring the situation, while over 7,000 relief camps in Odisha have been established to aid affected residents.
title: PM Modi, Amit Shah call Odisha CM as Cyclone Dana nears

description: Jitan Ram Manjhi responded to Tejashwi Yadav's claim that more people consume alcohol in Bihar than Maharashtra despite prohibition. Manjhi suggested Yadav might be involved in smuggling. Yadav cited a National Family Health Survey report and criticized the Nitish Kumar government over alleged corruption and failures related to the liquor ban, including rising rural liquor shops.
title: On liquor ban charges, Manjhi says Tejashwi 'may be involved in smuggling'

description: In a historic moment, spinners Sajid Khan and Noman Ali opened the bowling for Pakistan against England in Rawalpindi, marking only the second time in Test history with no pace bowling in the first innings. The spin-friendly pitch saw 13 wickets fall, with only one taken by a fast bowler.
title: England's first innings sees no pace for only second time

description: Canada will decrease its immigration targets by 21% over the next three years, aiming for 1.14 million permanent residents by 2025-2027. Measures include reducing temporary residents and stricter regulations for hiring overseas workers, focusing on sustainable population growth and addressing labor needs without straining resources.
title: Trudeau rolls-up welcome mat for immigrants after support plunges

description: India women's cricket team triumphed in the first ODI against New Zealand by 59 runs at Narendra Modi Stadium. Radha Yadav claimed 3 wickets, while debutant Saima Thakor made an impact. Despite India's batting struggles, notable starts and partnerships secured a competitive total.
title: Deepti stars as India beat New Zealand to take 1-0 series lead

description: Indian High Commissioner to Canada Sanjay Verma highlights Indian students' struggles in Canada, citing substandard living conditions, underemployment, and the influence of Khalistani elements as major issues, expressing concerns about safety and future prospects for these students.
title: Envoy Verma's stark warning for parents sending kids to Canada

description: The diplomatic conflict between India and Canada has escalated as New Delhi recalled six diplomats and expelled Canadian envoys. The spat erupted after Canadian PM Justin Trudeau accused India of being involved in the assassination of a Khalistani leader without providing concrete evidence, straining bilateral relations.
title: India-Canada ties: 'The onus is on Trudeau to clean up the mess'

description: Washington Sundar took seven wickets for India against New Zealand on Thursday in the second Test. Playing alongside R Ashwin and Ravindra Jadeja, Sundar achieved his career-best figures. India restricted New Zealand to 259 before reaching 16/1 at stumps in Pune. Sundar expressed his gratitude and highlighted his bowling technique and future expectations.
title: 'Manifested for this to happen': Sundar after 7/59

description: Here’s a roundup of today’s top five entertainment headlines, delivering the latest buzz from the world of movies, celebrities, and pop culture. From Salman Khan offering a blank cheque to the Bishnois to settle an ongoing dispute, to Dimple Kapadia declining to pose with daughter Twinkle Khanna, and Esha Deol sharing how Hema Malini told her about Dharmendra’s first wife — these are the top stories making waves in the entertainment world today!
title: Salman Khan offered a blank cheque to Bishnois, Dimple Kapadia refuses to pose with Twinkle Khanna, Esha Deol on learning about Dharmendra's first wife: Top 5 entertainment news

description: Zomato clarified that the Rs 10 platform fee hike is not a rumor and is a routine business adjustment. Both Zomato and Swiggy have increased platform fees in some cities to cover operational costs during the festive season. Zomato mentioned that this hike is temporary, while Swiggy has not provided any such clarification.
title: Zomato gives a clarification to BSE on platform fee hike

description: Justice Sanjiv Khanna is set to become the next Chief Justice of India, taking over from CJI DY Chandrachud on November 11. Justice Khanna, currently serving as a Supreme Court judge, was recommended by CJI Chandrachud and has been officially appointed by the President.  Justice Khanna was elevated as a Judge of the Supreme Court on January 18, 2019.
title: Justice Sanjiv Khanna is new CJI, to take oath on Nov 11
Army vehicle attacked by terrorists in J&K's Baramulla; 4 soldiers hurt, 1 civilian killed

description: Reliance has denied a Delhi-based app developer's request for funding his Cambridge EMBA studies in exchange for the jiohotstar.com domain. Despite contacting an executive, the £93,345 request has been refused and Reliance plans legal action. The developer claims no trademark infringement and seeks legal advice.
title: Techie who bought JioHotstar domain seeking funding for studies has an update

description: Union minister Shivraj Singh Chouhan, BJP's Jharkhand poll in charge, criticizes the Hemant Soren-led JMM government, comparing its rule to a destructive cyclone and accusing it of corruption and dynastic politics. Assembly elections in Jharkhand are set to take place in two phases on November 13 and November 20. Results will be announced on November 23.
title: 'Deadlier than Dana': Chouhan warns against voting for JMM in J'khand polls

description: Nvidia CEO Jensen Huang, at the Nvidia AI Summit 2024 in Mumbai, shared insights from his meetings with PM Modi. Modi emphasized the importance of India developing its own AI infrastructure, highlighting the need for India to add value to its data rather than exporting it for external AI solutions.
title: What Nvidia CEO told Mukesh Ambani about his first meeting with PM Modi

description: Cyclonic storm Dana is rapidly approaching Odisha's coast, anticipated to land between Bhitarkanika in Kendrapara and Dhamra in Bhadrak with winds up to 120 kmph. Odisha has evacuated 3 lakh people, prepared over 7,000 cyclone shelters, and ensured the safety of pregnant women. West Bengal also plans to evacuate 3.5 lakh people ahead of the storm.
title: Cyclone Dana approaches Odisha coast: Satellite view of monster storm

description: Indian envoy Sanjay Verma criticized Canada's leniency towards Khalistani terrorists, accusing them of human trafficking and funding extremism. He questioned Canada’s investigation into Hardeep Singh Nijjar's murder and condemned Nijjar's extrajudicial killing, labeling Canada’s move to implicate Indian diplomats as unprofessional and politically motivated for electoral gains.
title: How Khalistanis made Canada their stronghold: Recalled envoy Sanjay Verma explains

description: Washington Sundar shone bright with seven wickets, as his return helped India dismiss New Zealand for 259 on day one of the second Test. Supported by Ravichandran Ashwin’s three wickets, Sundar’s performance highlights India's bowling attack. India ended the day at 16/1, trailing by 243 runs.
title: Sundar relishes 'unbelievable feeling' after career-best figures

description: Telugu film 'Pushpa 2: The Rule' is now set to release a day earlier on December 5 in India and December 4 internationally. Directed by Sukumar, the sequel to the 2021 blockbuster features Allu Arjun, Rashmika Mandanna, and others, with music by Devi Sri Prasad.
title: 'Pushpa 2: The Rule': Makers announce new release date with poster

description: India captain Rohit Sharma was dismissed for a duck by New Zealand's Tim Southee on the first day of the second Test in Pune. Washington Sundar impressed with figures of 7-59 as India bowled out New Zealand for 259. At stumps, India was 16 for 1, trailing by 243 runs.
title: Southee stuns Rohit with an absolute jaffa, Pune crowd in disbelief

description: Travis Kelce and Taylor Swift are implementing a strict diet to enhance Kelce's football performance after a sluggish season start due to their summer parties. Swift is committed to supporting this change, aiming to eliminate unhealthy habits. Fans hope this renewed focus on health will recapture Kelce's competitive edge and benefit his game.
title: Taylor, Travis' health shift raises eyebrows amid NFL challenges

description: Union Defence Minister Rajnath Singh highlighted the India-China agreement easing border tensions as a result of dialogue. The pact, endorsed by PM Modi and President Xi Jinping, focuses on patrolling and grazing in traditional areas. This landmark agreement aims to restore peace along the LAC after prolonged military standoffs and deadly clashes in Galwan Valley.
title: 'Power of dialogue': Rajnath Singh's first reaction to LAC pact

description: Bushra Bibi, the wife of former Pakistani Prime Minister Imran Khan, was granted bail and released after nine months in custody related to the Toshakhana corruption case. The Islamabad high court judge granted bail with a Rs 1 million surety bond, and the indictment has been rescheduled for October 26 due to security concerns.
title: Imran Khan's wife Bushra Bibi freed from jail on bail in Toshakhana case

description: Cyclone Dana is set to hit Odisha's coast with wind speeds up to 120 km/h between Thursday night and Friday morning, leading to heavy rain and potential flooding. The state has evacuated over a million people and deployed numerous emergency teams. West Bengal will also face heavy rainfall, and significant disruptions are expected in both regions.
title: Cyclone Dana FAQs: Where will the cyclone make its landfall

description: Washington Sundar's career-best 7/59 helped India bowl out New Zealand for 259 in the second Test in Pune. India, however, faced an early setback as skipper Rohit Sharma was dismissed for a duck by Tim Southee. By stumps, India was at 16/1, with Sundar and Ashwin dominating the day's play.
title: 2nd Test: India suffer early blow after Sundar's masterclass on Day 1

description: Air India alerts passengers to intermittent issues with its contact centers, attributing the disruptions to technical difficulties. The airline assures customers that efforts are underway to resolve the problem. The company assured customers that their team is actively working to resolve the issue as quickly as possible and expressed appreciation for their patience during the disruption.
title: Air India customer centres face technical issues, services impacted

description: During the second Test against New Zealand in Pune, Rishabh Pant humorously advised Washington Sundar to deliver fuller balls, only to see Ajaz Patel hit a boundary. Sundar excelled with a seven-wicket haul as New Zealand were bowled out for 259, with India trailing by 243 runs at day's end.
title: 'Mereko kya pata issey Hindi aati hai': Pant's advice to Sundar backfires

description: Megan Garcia is suing Character.AI for allegedly causing her son's suicide after he became deeply attached to a chatbot. The lawsuit claims the chatbot misrepresented itself as a real person and engaged in inappropriate interactions.
title: Mother adds Google in lawsuit, blames chatbot for causing son's suicide

description: Sunil Gavaskar has praised Washington Sundar's addition to India's lineup for the second Test against New Zealand, calling it an 'inspired selection.' Despite initial criticism, Sundar silenced his skeptics by taking his first five-wicket haul in Tests, helping India dismiss New Zealand for 259. His performance highlights the debate around his selection over Kuldeep Yadav.
title: Washington Sundar takes 7/59, Sunil Gavaskar makes U-turn

description: Washington Sundar's impressive return to the Indian Test team saw him clinch a career-best figure of 7/59, dismantling New Zealand for 259 runs in the first innings. His performance included five clean bowled dismissals showcasing expert drift and turn, marking his first five-wicket haul in Tests. Sundar, who returned with best first-class figures of 7/59, led the team off the field for turning the game on its head.
title: Washington makes 'ati' Sundar comeback for career best Test figures

description: The Supreme Court issued a notice to Maharashtra deputy CM Ajit Pawar and his NCP faction to respond to a plea by Sharad Pawar's group regarding the use of the "clock" symbol. Ajit Pawar must ensure compliance with the court's interim order, permitting the symbol's use with a sub-judice notice.
title: SC allows Ajit Pawar faction to use clock symbol, but with a condition

description: Prime Minister Justin Trudeau's linguistic blunder, using the non-existent word 'brokenist,' became a highlight in a Parliament debate. Conservative leader Pierre Poilievre capitalized on the gaffe, further criticizing Trudeau amidst internal party pressure for him to step down before the upcoming election.
title: Trudeau under fire: 'Brokenist' slip sparks laughter as liberals face criticism

description: PM Narendra Modi-led Cabinet has approved two major railway projects: the 87 km Amaravati Railway Line in Andhra Pradesh at Rs 2,245 crore, connecting major cities and ports; and a 256 km double line railway in North Bihar to the Northeastern states at Rs 4,553 crore, improving connectivity and infrastructure for essential goods transport.
title: Cabinet approves new rail projects in Andhra and Bihar for Rs 6,798 cr

description: Indian airlines, including Vistara and IndiGo, faced threats on social media targeting around 20 flights each on October 24, 2024. Authorities were alerted, and security protocols were followed without diversions. Airlines urge the identification and arrest of the culprits to ensure strict action.
title: Mass bomb threats to over 80 flights again, mostly from same X account

description: The National Testing Agency (NTA) has revealed that any potential changes to the NEET UG 2025 exam pattern are pending a report from a High-Powered Expert Committee, as directed by the Supreme Court. This information surfaced following an RTI filed by Dr. Vivek Pandey, who sought minutes from meetings discussing the exam changes. The committee’s report is expected soon, leaving NEET aspirants awaiting updates. Recent changes to the JEE Main 2025 pattern have added to the anticipation.
title: NTA reveals changes to NEET UG 2025 exam pattern: Will it be altered?
J&K: Policeman injured in grenade explosion at Baramulla court evidence room

description: Robert Vadra expressed joy over Priyanka Gandhi Vadra's nomination for the Wayanad Lok Sabha by-elections, remarking that her father, Rajiv Gandhi, would have been proud. Vadra remains focused on charity but is open to considering politics if public and familial support align.
title: 'Had Rajiv ji been alive ...': Robert Vadra on wife Priyanka's nomination

description: An Indian tech professional in New York has sparked an online debate after expressing a preference for returning to India even with her $105,000 salary. She argued that New York's high cost of living prevents a luxurious lifestyle, prompting vigorous discussions about the balance between salary and quality of life, and the challenges of major Indian cities.
title: I would go back to India if ..., says techie earning Rs 88 lakh

description: A fire broke out at Iran's Karaj nuclear power plant amid reports of a terrorist attack. This follows deadly violence in Turkey, where an aviation firm's headquarters was attacked, prompting Turkish airstrikes on suspected Kurdish targets in Syria and Iraq. The Karaj facility was previously attacked in 2022.
title: Watch: Fire erupts at Iran's Karaj nuclear power plant

description: Prem Watsa, CEO of Fairfax Financial Holdings, has expressed confidence in India's potential to achieve double-digit economic growth under Prime Minister Narendra Modi. Praising initiatives like Make in India and StartUp India, Watsa believes that India, with its smart and hardworking populace, can sustainably reach 10% annual growth, transforming it into a developed nation by 2047.
title: Canada’s ‘Warren Buffett’ says ‘PM Modi is fantastic’; India can grow at 10%

description: Spinners Sajid Khan and Noman Ali dismantled England's batting lineup in Rawalpindi, leaving them reeling at 98 for five on the opening day of the third Test. Pakistan's keeper Rizwan cheekily mocked England's Bazball approach as the visitors struggled, with key players falling cheaply.
title: 'No more Bazball': Rizwan taunts England after collapse

description: Maharashtra Congress President Nana Patole confirmed the seat-sharing agreement among the Maha Vikas Agadhi (MVA) allies, with each party contesting 85 seats. The MVA's chief ministerial candidate will be decided post-election. Shiv Sena (UBT) announced its initial list of candidates, including Aaditya Thackeray. Nomination for 288 assembly seats is ongoing; polling is set for November 20.
title: Seat sharing finalised for MVA but who is CM face? What Nana Patole said

description: During the 16th BRICS summit in Russia's Kazan, Indian External Affairs Minister S Jaishankar emphasized India's call for reforms in both permanent and non-permanent categories of the UN Security Council, as well as the need to update the procedures of multilateral development banks.
title: Jaishankar pitches for reforms in UNSC at Brics Plus Summit

description: More than 70 flights from various Indian airlines, including Air India, Vistara, and IndiGo, received bomb threats on Thursday, involving emergency responses and tightened security. Around 250 flights have faced threats in the past 11 days. Civil Aviation authorities are introducing legislative measures and enhanced security protocols to tackle the ongoing wave of online threats.
title: No end to chaos: More than 70 flights receive fresh bomb threats

description: BJP has announced candidates for assembly by-polls in Rajasthan and Uttar Pradesh. Karilal Nanoma will contest from Chorasi (ST) in Rajasthan, while Uttar Pradesh sees seven candidates including Ramvir Singh and Suchismita Maurya. Deputy CM Brajesh Pathak expresses confidence in BJP's victory, attributing it to PM Modi's welfare schemes.
title: BJP releases list of candidates for Uttar Pradesh, Rajasthan bypolls

description: A US teen, infatuated with an AI chatbot modeled after Game of Thrones character Daenerys Targaryen, took his own life. His parents are suing Character AI, claiming the chatbot facilitated intimate and sexual conversations, leading to their son's death. Character AI plans to enhance safety features.
title: US teen kills himself after falling in love with GOT AI chatbot

description: Ravichandran Ashwin has surpassed Nathan Lyon, becoming the seventh-highest wicket-taker in Test cricket history with 531 wickets. His pivotal performance during India's second Test against New Zealand has solidified his standing as one of the game's premier off-spinners, contributing crucial breakthroughs and extending his tally in the World Test Championship.
title: Ahead of BGT, Ashwin surpasses Lyon to become...

description: Virat Kohli shared an emotional moment with Anushka Sharma after scoring a century at the 2022 Asia Cup, ending a two-year gap.  The moment was surreal for Kohli. He described how, upon reaching the milestone, he found himself laughing at the culmination of two years of hard work and longing.
title: Kohli reveals he was in tears while speaking to Anushka after scoring century

description: Navya Haridas, BJP's candidate for Wayanad Lok Sabha constituency, filed her nomination papers with senior party leaders. She emphasized the need for political change, criticizing past MPs for neglecting local issues. Haridas is set to face Congress' Priyanka Gandhi and LDF's Sathyan Mokeri in the upcoming election on November 13.
title: 'People of Wayanad require change': BJP candidate Navya Haridas files nomination

description: India, trailing 1-0 against New Zealand, made three significant changes for the second Test in Pune as Akash Deep replaced out-of-form Mohammed Siraj, Shubman Gill came in for KL Rahul, and all-rounder Washington Sundar was included for Kuldeep Yadav. In 2024, an out-of-form Siraj had multiple below-par outings in the longest format at home which were a cause for concern for the Indian team.
title: Explained: Why Siraj was walking a tight rope at home

description: Reliance Jio, Bharti Airtel, and Vodafone Idea are warning of potential service disruptions as TRAI's new traceability rules for messages come into effect. This could impact essential notifications like bank transactions and delivery updates. Telecom operators urge for a deadline extension, citing the need for more time to implement the necessary technical solutions.
title: Jio, Airtel & Vi caution TRAI of 'OTP blackouts’; seek deadline extension

description: Justice Juvvadi Sridevi of the Telangana High Court has granted bail to Tollywood choreographer Shaik Jani Basha, known as Jani Master, in a POCSO case. The assistant choreographer alleged rape, but his lawyer argued conflicting evidence on her age and consensual ties. The judge mandated that Jani Master and his family avoid interfering with the complainant's life.
title: Telangana HC grants bail to choreographer Jani Master

description: The Supreme Court Bar Association (SCBA) criticizes the unconsulted 'Lady Justice' statue changes and new museum plans in India's Supreme Court. The statue, lacking blindfold and sword but adorned with a crown, sparks debate among the legal community about tradition and symbolism in justice representation.
title: 'Clueless on rationale behind changes': SCBA on new Lady Justice statue and emblem

description: The National Payments Corporation of India has ordered fintech firms to stop using UPI APIs for unauthorised purposes, such as user authentication. This violates NPCI and RBI guidelines, and firms must comply or face penalties or cessation of UPI services.
title: NPCI sends 'warning letter' to fintechs: Ban for this 'unauthorised' UPI IDs use

description: Spin all-rounder Washington Sundar delivered a remarkable off-spinner's ball to dismiss New Zealand's Rachin Ravindra for 65 in the second Test in Pune. Sundar's delivery turned sharply to knock off Ravindra's stump, giving India a crucial breakthrough as New Zealand reached 201 for five at the end of the second session.
title: Watch: Sundar bamboozles Rachin with an absolute ripper

description: Silver vs gold: Silver has outperformed traditional equities, with a 33.65% rise since early 2024 and a 12.5% gain in the past month. Analysts suggest it as a strong diversification option due to growing industrial demand and potential Fed rate cuts.
title: Forget gold! Why silver may be a better investment right now

description: Heavy downpours in Bengaluru caused severe waterlogging, forcing a closure on one side of the Electronics City flyover. The resulting traffic standstill saw commuters trapped for hours, leading many to walk home. The Bengaluru traffic police have issued alternate route advisories for affected commuters.
title: IT hub to traffic hub: Stuck in Bengaluru's jam for hours, commuters abandon cars

description: Delhi High Court issued notices to the Centre and private entities over a plea to regulate concert ticket resales and block illegal ticket-selling sites. The petition highlights inflated resale prices for recent concerts and calls for a legal framework to curb ticket scalping, protect consumers, and integrate ticket revenue into the formal economy.
title: HC issues notice to Centre on plea to regulate Coldplay, Diljit ticket resales

description: Vivek Ramaswamy condemns Kamala Harris for comparing Trump to Hitler, calling it reckless and warning it could incite violence. This follows Harris's remarks about Trump's dangerous rhetoric and alleged admiration for Hitler, urging the need for apologies 13 days before the election.
title: 'Comparing Trump to Hitler not only ... ': Ramaswamy asks Harris to apologise

description: India made significant changes for the second Test against New Zealand in Pune, bringing in Akash Deep, Washington Sundar, and Shubman Gill. New Zealand, having won the first Test in Bengaluru, chose to bat first. Both teams made strategic adjustments due to injuries and pitch conditions, aiming for better performances in Pune.
title: Did India press panic button? Rohit Sharma announces three big changes

description: Ahead of the election, VP Kamala Harris held a town hall in Pennsylvania, addressing pivotal issues such as border security, the economy, abortion rights, and the Israeli-Palestinian conflict. She outlined her distinct policy priorities and criticised Donald Trump, emphasising a new approach if she assumes the presidency.
title: 5 key takeaways from Kamala Harris' CNN town hall

description: North Korean soldiers have traveled to Russia and could soon join the fight against Ukraine, making them legitimate military targets, according to the White House. The soldiers are receiving training in Russia, and this cooperation violates multiple UN security council resolutions. The U.S. is closely monitoring this situation and coordinating with allies on potential responses.
title: 'If N Korean soldiers joining Russia to fight Ukraine is true ...': White House

description: After a remarkable 150 in Bengaluru, Sarfaraz Khan was included in the playing XI for the second Test in Pune. His performance under pressure led India's comeback, placing him over KL Rahul. Sarfaraz's consistent domestic cricket success makes him a strong contender for a permanent middle-order spot in India's Test squad.
title: Sarfaraz Khan over KL Rahul: Team India sends a strong message

description: In Pune's Pimpri Chinchwad township, a makeshift water tank collapsed in the Bhosari area, killing three labourers and injuring seven others. The incident occurred while the labourers were bathing under the tank, which reportedly exploded due to water pressure, trapping and fatally wounding some of the workers.
title: 3 dead, 7 injured as water tank collapses on labourer's camp in Pune

description: Mariel Garza, editorials editor of the LA Times, resigned after the paper's owner, Patrick Soon-Shiong, blocked the board's endorsement of Kamala Harris for president. Garza cited a need to stand up during 'dangerous times.' The decision has sparked concerns within the Times Guild.
title: Los Angeles Times editorial chief resigns over Harris endorsement

description: BJP spokesperson Pradeep Bhandari criticized Priyanka Gandhi's decision to contest from Wayanad, attributing it to a high Muslim vote bank and following her brother Rahul Gandhi's success. He labeled Congress as a 'modern Muslim League,' alleging attempts to divide Hindu society. Meanwhile, Priyanka expressed gratitude and assured to address Wayanad's concerns.
title: 'Priyanka ran away to Wayanad because ... ': BJP calls Congress 'modern Muslim League'

description: England’s cricket team demonstrated exceptional teamwork by rearranging chairs after their team photo ahead of the third Test against Pakistan. With the series tied 1-1, England aims to regain momentum despite facing spin challenges. Captain Ben Stokes emphasizes strategic adaptations, while Pakistan remains confident with an unchanged XI. Both teams seek a crucial victory on a variable Rawalpindi pitch.
title: Viral Video: England players carry chairs in Pakistan
5 dead, 1 injured after car overturns after tyre burst in Rajasthan's Sirohi

description: Canadian MP Chandra Arya acknowledges the issue of Khalistani extremism, citing personal experiences and calling for serious action from law enforcement. Tensions between Canada and India have escalated over allegations of Indian involvement in the death of terrorist Hardeep Singh Nijjar, which India refutes.
title: We have serious problem of Khalistani extremism: Canadian MP Chandra Arya

description: Marriage rituals worldwide vary widely, from napping dishes in Germany symbolizing teamwork to Scotland's messy 'blackening the bride' tradition. Indian weddings often include a playful ritual of stealing the groom's shoes. Some customs, like bride kidnapping in Kyrgyzstan and Bihar, are thankfully now illegal, emphasizing diverse ways cultures celebrate marriage.
title: 5 strange wedding rituals from different cultures that will surprise you

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi greeted the Indo-Tibetan Border Police on its 63rd Raising Day, praising their valour and dedication in protecting the nation under harsh conditions. Union ministers Amit Shah, Kiren Rijiju, and Dharmendra Pradhan also lauded the ITBP's bravery and sacrifice. The Force reiterated its commitment to national security, honouring the personnel who serve in the most challenging terrains.
title: PM Modi lauds ITBP 'Himveers' on 63rd Raising Day

description: India seamer Harshit Rana will leave the Test set-up to play for Delhi in the Ranji Trophy against Assam at Arun Jaitley Stadium. With Navdeep Saini in the India A squad, Rana will boost Delhi's pace attack. Other roster changes include Dhruv Kaushik's injury replacement and the addition of fit-again seamer Money Grewal.
title: Harshit to be released from India Test set-up for Ranji game

description: Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau faces a significant internal challenge as fellow party members urged him to consider resignation during a private Liberal caucus meeting. A critical document and a letter signed by two dozen MPs highlight growing concerns over the party's declining poll numbers and upcoming election prospects.
title: Why Trudeau’s party MPs want him to quit as Canada PM by October 28

description: During a rally in Duluth, Donald Trump humorously asked for an immigration chart to be removed so he could see himself, remarking on his hair. Kamala Harris’ campaign mocked him as lost and confused. Former independent candidate Robert F Kennedy Jr joined Trump, while Harris labeled Trump a fascist at a CNN town hall.
title: 'Oooooh...I don't like my hair': Trump gets distracted mid-speech at rally; see video

description: Ravichandran Ashwin provided India with an early breakthrough by dismissing New Zealand captain Tom Latham for 15 runs, followed by the wicket of Will Young. Ashwin's precision spin on the leg stump and sharp turn led to effective lbw and catch dismissals, solidifying India's position in the second Test against New Zealand.
title: Watch: Ashwin gives India first breakthrough in 2nd Test

description: Delhi's air quality remains in the 'very poor' category with AQI levels over 330. Environment Minister Gopal Rai attributes the worsening pollution to northwesterly winds carrying stubble burn effects from Haryana and Punjab. He urges actions including banning diesel vehicles and exploring artificial rain solutions.
title: Delhi's air pollution woes continue, AQI still in 'very poor' zone

description: Sunil Gavaskar criticises India's decision to exclude Kuldeep Yadav in favor of Washington Sundar for the second Test against New Zealand, viewing it as a sign of panic. He believes Yadav's left-arm wrist spin was crucial against New Zealand’s left-handers. India, trailing in the series, must win to protect their home record and WTC final hopes.
title: 'India are worried ...': Gavaskar criticises Sundar's inclusion

description: In Greater Noida, police arrested two men after discovering a property dealer's body in a burnt SUV. Sanjay Yadav, identified through the vehicle's registration, was allegedly killed for his jewelry by Vishal Rajput and Jeet Chaudhary, who strangled him and set the car on fire.
title: The burning Fortuner: 'Realtor choked to death by pals after beer party'

description: Shubam Kumar, a labourer from Uttar Pradesh, was shot by terrorists in Pulwama's Tral area, sustaining injuries to his arm. This attack is the third in a week targeting non-local labourers in Kashmir, following fatal attacks in Ganderbal and Shopian districts. Kumar is receiving treatment at a nearby hospital.
title: UP labourer shot by terrorists in Pulwama, third attack in past one week

description: The Supreme Court has expressed frustration over the failure of the Centre, CAQM, and Punjab and Haryana governments to control stubble burning, stating that citizens have a fundamental right to a pollution-free environment. The court insists on increasing penalties and criticizes the lack of effective measures and penal action against farmers.
title: Farm-fire action just eyewash; clean air is a fundamental right: Supreme Court

description: Ahead of the second Test in Pune, Rohit Sharma addressed the KL Rahul vs Sarfaraz Khan debate by choosing Sarfaraz, who has consistently performed. Despite being supported by the team, pressure mounts on KL Rahul due to his recent lack of form in Test cricket. Former India cricketer Aakash Chopra believes that time is running out for KL Rahul, who has struggled in red-ball cricket recently.
title: 'Time is running out': Ex-cricketer's big take on KL Rahul

description: A recent Delhi video shows Sachin Raj harassing a foreign tourist while filming a dance reel, sparking backlash and leading him to disable comments. The incident is part of a worrying trend, similar to a June case in Jaipur involving harassment for social media notoriety.
title: Man chases foreign tourist, dances around her for Instagram reel in Delhi

description: Ravichandran Ashwin, India's top off-spinner, has become the leading wicket-taker in the ICC World Test Championship. He surpassed Australia's Nathan Lyon during the second Test against New Zealand in Pune. Ashwin's tally reached 188 wickets in 39 matches. He continues to play a crucial role in India's bowling attack in the WTC.
title: Record Alert! Ashwin becomes leading wicket-taker in WTC

description: In Chhattisgarh's Sakti district, a school bus with 18 children plunged into the Son river, but quick action by villagers saved all the kids. The bus was submerged, and locals dived in to rescue the students, who are expected to fully recover. Authorities will re-conduct fitness tests for school vehicles, and investigations into the accident are ongoing.
title: Mere seconds and brave villagers: Quick action saves 18 kids from drowning

description: At least five people were killed and 22 others injured in a terror attack at Turkish Aerospace Industries' headquarters near Ankara. The attackers, identified as a man and a woman, were killed. Turkish authorities suspect the Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) and have launched retaliatory airstrikes in Iraq and Syria.
title: Turkey attack: CCTV captures terrorists carrying guns storming TUSAS HQ

description: Nilesh Rane, son of BJP MP Narayan Rane, joined Shiv Sena ahead of the Maharashtra assembly elections, motivated by the Mahayuti alliance's seat-sharing arrangement. His induction was marked by a rally in Kudal, with significant support reported by Maharashtra chief minister Eknath Shinde.
title: Nilesh Rane, son of ex-CM Narayan Rane, joins Shiv Sena

description: BJP's Tamil Nadu unit accuses the ruling DMK of posting a map excluding Pakistan Occupied Kashmir and Aksai Chin, labelling it a betrayal of India's sovereignty. The BJP condemns this act, alongside past anti-national activities attributed to DMK. They demand an unconditional apology from DMK chief MK Stalin and call for national unity to protect India's integrity.
title: BJP hits out at DMK for allegedly sharing map excluding PoK, Aksai Chin

description: Former Union minister P Chidambaram criticizes J&K LG Manoj Sinha for holding a security review meeting without elected CM Omar Abdullah, highlighting the lack of authority of the CM. Chidambaram calls for the immediate restoration of full statehood to Jammu and Kashmir.
title: 'J&K CM has no authority': Chidambaram slams LG for security meeting without Omar

description: The government is considering raising the VPF limit for tax-free interest under EPFO to incentivize savings among lower-middle and middle-income salaried individuals. The current cap, introduced to prevent high-income earners from using this provision, taxes interest on contributions exceeding Rs 2.5 lakh.
title: Cheer for middle income salaried class soon? This limit may be hiked…

description: In a crucial moment during the second Test in Pune, Sarfaraz Khan convinced Rohit Sharma to review a caught-behind decision, successfully dismissing Will Young. Sarfaraz's confidence, backed by Virat Kohli, led to Ashwin’s second wicket of the session, with New Zealand at 92 for 2 at lunch.
title: Sarfaraz pleads Rohit to take review. Watch video

description: Political tensions mount in Delhi as BJP and AAP blame each other for worsening air and water pollution. BJP's Sachdeva protests against the AAP-led government, accusing it of mismanaging the Yamuna River cleanup. AAP attributes pollution issues to industrial activities and stubble burning in BJP-ruled states.
title: Delhi pollution: BJP's Virendra Sachdeva protests by taking dip in toxic Yamuna

description: Aam Aadmi Party Convenor Arvind Kejriwal will campaign for INDIA bloc candidates in Maharashtra and Jharkhand, focusing on seats where AAP has a strong volunteer base. Kejriwal, alongside senior AAP leaders, will support candidates without controversial backgrounds within alliances like Shiv Sena-UBT and JMM. Assembly elections in both states are set for November.
title: Kejriwal to campaign for INDIA bloc in Maharashtra, Jharkhand

description: Parliament's Public Accounts Committee has postponed a meeting with Sebi chairperson Madhabi Puri Buch, who couldn't attend. The agenda included reviewing the performance of regulatory bodies. Buch and her husband recently denied allegations of improper income from ICICI Bank and ICICI Prudential after retirement.
title: PAC meeting postponed as Sebi chief Madhabi Puri Buch fails to attend

description: A video by Pakistani content creator Rana Hamza Saif showcasing China's innovative palm payment system has gone viral. Filmed in Zhuzhou, it captures Saif and friends making payments with the wave of a hand.
title: Pak influencer's video on China: "Yeh Hamare Liye Bahut Hairaani wali baat hai"

description: Long-term mental wellbeing is driven more by good workplace relationships and pride in work rather than factors like workload and flexibility, according to a global study. In India, office workers showed better mental health than remote workers, highlighting the significance of team dynamics.
title: Why WFO may be better than WFH for mental health

description: Vikash Yadav's lawyers argue he is being used as a 'scapegoat' in an international conspiracy, denying US allegations of a plot to assassinate Gurpatwant Singh Pannun. They stress Yadav's innocence, citing no US travel history, and emphasize the severe personal and psychological toll on him.
title: Vikash Yadav innocent, being made a 'scapegoat', say his lawyers
Government slams Meta, X for 'not aiding' bomb hoax probe

description: India and China reached a milestone agreement to end the prolonged military standoff in eastern Ladakh, endorsed by PM Narendra Modi and President Xi Jinping. The leaders held a 50-minute meeting, underscoring the importance of strategic communication and cooperation. Special Representatives will soon resume talks on the boundary issue to maintain peace and stabilize bilateral relations.
title: LAC pact: China talks of ‘important progress’, not ‘agreement’

description: On Tuesday, an Urdu teacher in Ghaziabad faced harassment by a resident, Manoj Kumar, who demanded he chant 'Jai Shri Ram'. Kumar, later found to be intoxicated, was arrested and charged under various sections for wrongful restraint and intentional insult.
title: Urdu teacher accosted in Ghaziabad condo, told to say ‘Jai Shri Ram’ and leave

description: Akhilesh Yadav announced that all nine seats in the upcoming UP bypolls will be contested using the SP's 'bicycle' symbol, sidelining Congress in the India bloc alliance. While Congress was seeking at least three seats, SP's decision effectively ends discussions on seat-sharing arrangements.
title: INDIA bloc will contest in UP bypolls on SP cycle symbol: Akhilesh

description: A special court has framed charges against Congress MP Imran Masood for a decade-old speech during the 2014 Lok Sabha elections where he threatened violence against then Gujarat CM Narendra Modi. Masood faces multiple IPC sections and other charges, which he dismisses as politically motivated. The trial will proceed in the special MP/MLA court.
title: Charges framed against Congress MP Masood for 2014 ‘boti-boti’ jibe against Modi

description: Apple's first developer beta of iOS 18.2 brings new Apple Intelligence features, extending support to more English-speaking regions. Highlights include creative image generation tools, enhanced writing tools with ChatGPT integration, and Visual Intelligence for iPhone 16 series users. Expected by year's end, these features aim to enhance user experience significantly.
title: Apple releases iOS 18.2 beta with these new Apple Intelligence features

description: A Delhi-based app developer anticipated the merger between Reliance JioCinema and Disney+ Hotstar, purchasing the domain JioHotstar. He aims to use this potential windfall to fund his studies at Cambridge. The merger, completing regulatory approvals, is poised to form India’s top media conglomerate by November, with a valuation of $8.5 billion.
title: JioHotstar domain bought by app developer who wants Reliance to fund his studies
